how to identify the pattern "SLIDING WINDOW"
eg:1.fixed size window[subarray/substring of length k]
   if it is given to calculate sum or max of size k 
   if it is mentioned as subarray, substring
   [10,12,-5,-45,30]
   we have to calculate max avg of k=4
   10+12-5-45/4;
   for next we will start fromm i=1 12,-5,-45 is common hence we just add 30 and sub 10
   ques:643,246
2.Dynamic/variable window
   size is not fixed 
   ex:return the minimial len of a subarray whose sum is greater than or equal to target
   [2,3,1,,2,4,3]
   keep i and j at 0 index
   keep i at 0 and move j untill sum is >= 7
   ques:209,3
3.substring or subarray char freq cond
  at most k distinct chars
  eq:s1="ab" s2="eibaooo"
  return true if s2 contains a permutation of s1 false otherwise
  use hashmap matching because ab may be s1 but in s2 we may contain ba even if it is 
  true it returns false if we check chars
  ques:340,567

